Date: 19/8/1910
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: Some important legislative proposals are put forward in the Mining Amendment Bill brought down by Governor's Message in the House of Representatives yesterday. .. Where gold is associated with other metals or minerals, a special claim may be granted, and the holders of the claim will be entitled to all metals or minerals within the boundaries of the claim.
Notes:

Date: 26/11/1869
Source: West Coast Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: What is a special claim? One would consider it was an extended area, granted as a reward to persevering men who have succeeded in finding probable gold-producing quartz in places in which it was not generally known to exist.
Notes:

Date: 10/7/1875
Source: West Coast Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: A public meeting will be held at the Miners' Institute, Callaghan's, on Monday evening next, "to consider the proposal to cancel the special claim of the United Gold Mining Company, Callaghan's." This claim adjoins the Long Tunnel Claim, and the Company is on the eve of being floated.
Notes:

Date: 26/1/1895
Source: Thames Star
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: Sir,- In the up-country mining districts I notice that there are several applications for special claims for working old ground, &c., to consist of 100 acres. If these applications are granted it will mean the locking up and leaving unprospected for many years of vast areas of ground, and will cause incalculable injury to prospectors, miners, and the public generally.
Notes:

