Source: Otago Daily Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: An application was heard for the cancellation of the Great Western special claim. It was defended by the company, who contended that no provision is made in the Mines Act or regulations thereunder for hearing such application, the regulations applying only to leases.
